1
00:00:09,480 --> 00:00:10,440
Let us go.

2
00:00:10,440 --> 00:00:13,920
Let us out.

3
00:00:15,480 --> 00:00:16,320
Zhang Chao.

4
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:18,200
What do we do now?

5
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:21,080
We're locked in here and can't get out.

6
00:01:28,160 --> 00:01:29,240
Mr. and Mrs. Li.

7
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:31,960
Please don't be too sad.

8
00:01:32,880 --> 00:01:35,320
He left so suddenly,

9
00:01:35,320 --> 00:01:37,720
didn't leave a single word,

10
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:41,600
didn't even take a bite of his birthday cake.

11
00:01:42,520 --> 00:01:45,400
How can I not be sad?

12
00:01:47,720 --> 00:01:48,920
Chao.

13
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:51,039
The day of the accident was Xiao Hao's birthday.

14
00:01:51,039 --> 00:01:52,700
He specifically invited you.

15
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,800
Why didn't you come to our house?

16
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:58,450
I had my own things to do.

17
00:01:58,880 --> 00:02:01,160
And he considered you his best friend.

18
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:03,540
How could you treat him like this?

19
00:02:03,880 --> 00:02:05,740
How I treated him doesn't matter.

20
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:08,919
The last place he went wasn't my place.

21
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:10,680
What do you mean by that?

22
00:02:11,160 --> 00:02:11,520
Mr. Li.

23
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:14,320
Are you saying we parents caused Xiao Hao's death?

24
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:15,760
Mr. Li, calm down.

25
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:17,040
I'm his roommate.

26
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:18,440
I can testify that he never hurt Li Weihao.

27
00:02:18,440 --> 00:02:20,400
Don't touch me! Stay away from me!

28
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:23,000
But as for some people,

29
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,240
I'm not so sure.

30
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:29,520
Why are you looking at me?

31
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:31,840
Why do you think?

32
00:02:33,440 --> 00:02:34,900
What did you do to Xiao Hao?

33
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:36,960
Don't you know?

34
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:38,020
What did I do to him?

35
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:40,240
Is it wrong for me to help him make money?

36
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,200
Exactly.

37
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:43,760
Why are you so good at slinging mud, Zhang Chao?

38
00:02:43,760 --> 00:02:45,120
Li Weihao did all of that willingly.

39
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:46,050
Didn't you know?

40
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:47,920
Don't move.

41
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:49,450
Never seen such a loyal dog.

42
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:51,280
A loyal dog? Say that again!

43
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:52,240
Enough.

44
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:52,960
When he was alive,

45
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:54,200
you weren't exactly nice to him either.

46
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:54,800
Everyone, calm down!

47
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,200
What on earth did you do to him?

48
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:56,930
Lin Jiaming.

49
00:02:57,440 --> 00:02:58,900
What did you do to Xiao Hao?

50
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:01,080
What I did

51
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:03,700
is exactly what my dad made you do.

52
00:03:05,480 --> 00:03:06,800
Lin Jiaming!

53
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:08,000
I...

54
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:08,760
What?

55
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:10,200
Hit me!

56
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:11,680
Hit me!

57
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:18,840
You are all his roommates.

58
00:03:18,840 --> 00:03:19,640
My son's death

59
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:21,900
has something to do with every one of you.

60
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:24,320
You.

61
00:03:24,320 --> 00:03:26,160
None of you will get away with it.

62
00:03:26,160 --> 00:03:27,880
What kind of money did he help him make?

63
00:03:27,880 --> 00:03:29,200
What kind of money did he make?

64
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:30,640
Tell me!

65
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:35,800
A mother with narcissistic personality disorder,

66
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,400
plus a flying monkey father.

67
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:38,880
Just this kind of family of origin

68
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:40,240
is suffocating enough.

69
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:42,040
I used to just think

70
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:43,770
his mother was a control freak.

71
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:46,920
I never thought his father was an accomplice too.

72
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:49,000
His mother is more than just controlling.

73
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,160
Did you notice

74
00:03:50,160 --> 00:03:51,920
the scar on his mother's wrist?

75
00:03:55,680 --> 00:03:56,800
It's very likely

76
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:59,800
his mother manipulated Li Weihao through self-harm.

77
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:03,330
This piece is better. No bones.

78
00:04:03,480 --> 00:04:04,610
Son, have some fish.

79
00:04:05,320 --> 00:04:06,640
Alright, you eat some too.

80
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:07,640
Eat.

81
00:04:07,640 --> 00:04:09,040
You gave it all to our son.

82
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:10,040
Here you go.

83
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:12,840
Given Li Weihao's people-pleasing personality,

84
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:15,440
he will unknowingly be bled dry,

85
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:17,519
constantly sacrificing himself

86
00:04:17,519 --> 00:04:19,120
to maintain family harmony.

87
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:21,060
Having parents like these

88
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:23,640
is truly a child's lifelong nightmare.

89
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:25,200
That's why people say,

90
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:26,960
if a child in a family is sick,

91
00:04:26,960 --> 00:04:29,080
they must be the least sick of them all.

92
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:31,360
His parents are a child's first bullies.

93
00:04:32,159 --> 00:04:33,240
And then this child

94
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:36,400
will become a victim of school bullying.

95
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:38,760
It's a vicious cycle.

96
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:40,600
So you think

97
00:04:41,159 --> 00:04:42,640
Li Weihao's death

98
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:43,700
is related to them?

99
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:45,040
I'm not sure.

100
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:48,540
But from what I know about Weihao,

101
00:04:49,560 --> 00:04:52,020
he wouldn't kill himself over 100,000 yuan.

102
00:04:52,880 --> 00:04:54,680
Then it was because of bullying?

103
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:57,360
You mean Lin Jiaming?

104
00:04:57,760 --> 00:04:58,800
I did a little investigation

105
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,280
into this student Lin.

106
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:01,160
He's a repeat offender.

107
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:03,400
He has enjoyed bullying people since he was a child.

108
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:05,400
If his bullying is true,

109
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:07,040
I suggest we notify the school

110
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,570
and relevant authorities.

111
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:17,520
On the surface, he looks like a

112
00:05:17,520 --> 00:05:18,840
glamorous rich kid.

113
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:19,720
In reality,

114
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:21,040
he's a selfish, vain,

115
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:22,520
emotionally closed, unempathetic,

116
00:05:22,520 --> 00:05:24,160
amoral, manipulative

117
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:25,680
Machiavellian.

118
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:28,280
He must also be a victim of his family of origin.

119
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:49,320
But Li Weihao was about to leave Qiongzhou soon.

120
00:05:50,159 --> 00:05:51,520
Logically speaking,

121
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:52,920
school bullying

122
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:55,159
shouldn't have been such a big threat anymore.

123
00:05:55,159 --> 00:05:56,000
That's true.

124
00:05:58,560 --> 00:05:59,360
Have you noticed that

125
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:00,560
besides Li Weihao,

126
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,840
each of them has their own big problems?

127
00:06:05,320 --> 00:06:07,840
I feel the most normal one is Zhang Chao.

128
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:11,010
I think he is the most problematic one.

129
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:12,800
But

130
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:13,760
where the problem lies,

131
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:15,220
I haven't figured out yet.

132
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:48,659
Zhu Xiaoyu.

133
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,040
You scared me to death.

134
00:06:52,080 --> 00:06:53,340
Why didn't you call me?

135
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,280
Xiaohao

136
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:56,200
is dead.

137
00:06:59,120 --> 00:06:59,720
I know.

138
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:02,760
Mr. Bai said to give you some time off.

139
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:04,040
Get some good rest.

140
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:06,610
Don't come to me if it's not important.

141
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:13,520
I got Xiaohao's phone.

142
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:14,880
And then?

143
00:07:15,320 --> 00:07:16,720
He knew everything.

144
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:19,760
Did he leave any evidence?

145
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:21,020
Delete it quickly.

146
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:23,400
I did all this for him.

147
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:24,400
For my son.

148
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:25,800
I did all these dirty things.

149
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:27,720
How could he not understand?

150
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:28,800
Why couldn't he figure it out?

151
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:29,720
Are you crazy?

152
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:33,080
That's your family's mess.

153
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:34,640
It has nothing to do with me.

154
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:37,210
Don't come to me if it's not important.

155
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:16,100
Hello, President.

156
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:18,840
What did Jiaming do

157
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:20,440
the night before yesterday?

158
00:08:21,840 --> 00:08:23,920
The young master was discussing projects all night.

159
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:25,600
Keep a close eye on him.

160
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,320
Report to me

161
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:28,520
if anything happens.

162
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:31,440
Boss.

163
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:35,520
Boss.

164
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:37,520
Boss.

165
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,200
Something happened.

166
00:08:43,159 --> 00:08:44,080
What's going on?

167
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:45,400
Didn't Li Weihao commit suicide?

168
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:46,730
Who is this Lin Jiaming?

169
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:48,800
He is Li Weihao's roommate.

170
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:50,530
He used to bully Li Weihao a lot.

171
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:53,280
What are you filming?

172
00:08:53,280 --> 00:08:54,480
What's there to look at?

173
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:56,120
Do you have nothing better to do?

174
00:08:56,120 --> 00:08:58,380
What's so interesting to film, I ask you?

175
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:00,240
Stop filming.

176
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:01,300
I'm talking to you.

177
00:09:01,560 --> 00:09:02,280
Why are you still filming?

178
00:09:02,280 --> 00:09:03,360
I told you

179
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:04,200
not to film.

180
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,060
Go ahead, film.

181
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:06,440
Keep filming and this will happen to you.

182
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:07,240
Do you hear me?

183
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:08,240
I'm telling you,

184
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:10,040
whoever dares to film and post it online,

185
00:09:10,040 --> 00:09:11,840
your phone will end up like hers.

186
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,080
Don't worry, Boss.

187
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:21,650
I'll definitely find this guy for you.

188
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:45,400
Xiaoyu.

189
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:46,480
Xiaoyu.

190
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:47,120
Look.

191
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:51,000
· Thumbs Up Shoe Washing.

192
00:09:51,560 --> 00:09:52,880
Xiaoyu,

193
00:09:52,880 --> 00:09:54,800
is Mr. Lin really the murderer?

194
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:57,720
You are close to Mr. Lin.

195
00:09:57,720 --> 00:09:58,980
You must know, Xiaoyu.

196
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,360
How is that possible?

197
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:01,690
Given Mr. Lin's status,

198
00:10:02,040 --> 00:10:03,720
with his status,

199
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:04,840
killing him

200
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:06,930
would only dirty his hands.

201
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:18,840
Zhang Chao.

202
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,560
I haven't offended you, right?

203
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:21,400
You have now.

204
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:22,680
So what if I did?

205
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:25,240
Are you going to set me up again,

206
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:26,920
or scold me on the wall again?

207
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:30,760
I don't know what you're talking about.

208
00:10:30,760 --> 00:10:32,440
Stop pretending.

209
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:33,760
You don't understand?

210
00:10:33,760 --> 00:10:35,080
Where were you last night?

211
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:36,960
Did you write the graffiti on the wall?

212
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:38,020
I'm not that bored.

213
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:39,730
You say it was me.

214
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:41,560
Where is the evidence?

215
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:44,640
Evidence needs to be found.

216
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:46,360
Afu, if I'm right,

217
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:49,120
his mask should be in the closet.

218
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:50,080
Search it.

219
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:51,080
Okay.

220
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:54,680
What are you doing?

221
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:57,160
What's wrong?

222
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:58,840
You won't even let us look in the closet?

223
00:10:58,840 --> 00:10:59,770
Feeling guilty?

224
00:11:02,760 --> 00:11:03,620
Don't touch me.

225
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:05,360
I am not Li Weihao.

226
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:06,960
I won't let you two act crazy.

227
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:08,650
I'll only say this once.

228
00:11:08,680 --> 00:11:10,400
I don't have the mask here.

229
00:11:10,680 --> 00:11:12,610
And I didn't do the things you said.

230
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,440
But if you want trouble,

231
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:16,320
I'll play along to the end.

232
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:17,520
Then let me search it.

233
00:11:19,920 --> 00:11:21,040
What are you doing?

234
00:11:21,040 --> 00:11:21,920
Afu.

235
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:24,640
Let go!

236
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:32,210
I'll only say this once.

237
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:35,840
Li Weihao's death

238
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:38,160
has nothing to do with me.

239
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,320
But if you want to play,

240
00:11:41,520 --> 00:11:42,980
I'll play along to the end.

241
00:11:53,760 --> 00:11:54,840
Just wait and see.

242
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:01,960
Are you crazy?

243
00:12:08,280 --> 00:12:09,240
Boss.

244
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:10,960
Wasn't that person wearing a mask?

245
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:12,760
Why do you think it's Zhang Chao?

246
00:12:13,040 --> 00:12:14,240
Just a feeling.

247
00:12:15,520 --> 00:12:17,920
But he didn't look like he was lying just now.

248
00:12:17,920 --> 00:12:19,280
Did we get the wrong guy?

249
00:12:20,560 --> 00:12:21,800
If he does it once, he'll do it twice.

250
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:23,640
If he does it twice, he'll do it three times.

251
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:25,080
Running a horse in the clouds,

252
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:27,210
he'll expose himself sooner or later.

253
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:29,840
Dad.

254
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:42,280
I originally

255
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:44,560
came to the school to handle some business.

256
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:45,840
I didn't expect

257
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:48,800
you to give me such a surprise.

258
00:12:50,120 --> 00:12:52,280
Having your name written on the wall,

259
00:12:52,920 --> 00:12:53,850
how does it feel?

260
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:55,280
Dad, listen to me.

261
00:12:55,280 --> 00:12:56,880
Someone died at school recently,

262
00:12:56,880 --> 00:12:58,440
but it really has nothing to do with me.

263
00:12:58,440 --> 00:12:59,400
Lin Jiaming.

264
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:03,040
It doesn't matter whether you killed someone or not.

265
00:13:03,040 --> 00:13:05,100
Having your name written on the wall,

266
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:08,800
you didn't handle this smartly.

267
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:10,400
Dad, don't worry.

268
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:12,120
I've already found that person.

269
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:14,380
Can you use your brain when doing things?

270
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:17,160
What you need to solve

271
00:13:17,160 --> 00:13:18,890
is not the cause of this matter,

272
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:22,080
but the result.

273
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:23,640
I understand.

274
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:27,090
Find a way to settle these trivial matters yourself.

275
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:29,330
Don't affect the company's image.

276
00:13:30,440 --> 00:13:31,240
Also,

277
00:13:31,680 --> 00:13:34,360
don't always go to nightclubs to discuss business in the future.

278
00:13:34,360 --> 00:13:36,560
The driver goes to pick you up in the middle of the night,

279
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:38,480
it's hard on him too.

280
00:13:50,080 --> 00:13:50,800
Boss,

281
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:51,930
are you okay?

282
00:13:54,520 --> 00:13:55,320
I'm fine.

283
00:13:56,040 --> 00:13:58,040
I'm going to lay low for a couple of days.

284
00:13:58,040 --> 00:13:59,120
But before I leave,

285
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:02,280
I have one more thing to do.

286
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:12,240
Sir, should I keep driving?

287
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:13,200
Keep going.

288
00:14:13,640 --> 00:14:15,160
We'll hit the beach soon.

289
00:14:18,280 --> 00:14:19,010
Stop the car.

290
00:14:29,640 --> 00:14:31,970
Thanks for picking me up so late recently.

291
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:33,520
Take a good vacation

292
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:34,480
and rest.

293
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:36,920
Sir.

294
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:38,320
Sir!

295
00:14:38,560 --> 00:14:39,320
Sir!

296
00:15:13,880 --> 00:15:14,920
Hello.

297
00:15:15,360 --> 00:15:15,960
Miss,

298
00:15:16,360 --> 00:15:19,240
do you still want that subway apartment you reserved?

299
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:20,200
If you do,

300
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:22,860
let's sign a letter of intent when you have time.

301
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:35,250
Are you still there?

302
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:36,480
I'm sorry.

303
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:40,760
I don't need the apartment

304
00:15:40,760 --> 00:15:42,080
for now.

305
00:15:42,960 --> 00:15:45,090
Are you dissatisfied with something?

306
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:46,120
No,

307
00:15:46,120 --> 00:15:47,450
the apartment is great.

308
00:15:47,480 --> 00:15:48,440
It's just that

309
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:52,200
the person renting it can't come anymore.

310
00:15:54,320 --> 00:15:55,520
I'm sorry.

311
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:57,040
Goodbye.

312
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:41,240
Rice with chili sauce.

313
00:16:41,640 --> 00:16:44,300
Not many people from Qiongzhou like spicy food.

314
00:16:46,160 --> 00:16:46,960
Are you alone?

315
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:49,800
Can I sit here?

316
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:55,160
Suit yourself.

317
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:17,520
After seeing you in the counseling room last time,

318
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:20,079
I've been wanting to ask you out.

319
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:24,369
I'm not interested in older women.

320
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:29,400
I asked you out

321
00:17:29,400 --> 00:17:31,260
because you're Weihao's friend.

322
00:17:33,560 --> 00:17:35,120
I told you,

323
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:37,120
I said I'm not.

324
00:17:37,120 --> 00:17:38,320
You used to be.

325
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:43,080
Don't you want to know in Weihao's eyes,

326
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:45,100
what kind of person Zhang Chao is?

327
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:48,520
That Zhang Chao

328
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:50,100
is very righteous.

329
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:52,520
Whenever his friends are in danger,

330
00:17:52,920 --> 00:17:55,450
he steps in front of them without hesitation.

331
00:17:57,360 --> 00:17:58,680
That Zhang Chao

332
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:00,240
was very caring.

333
00:18:01,040 --> 00:18:03,770
He would feed the stray cats in the neighborhood.

334
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:05,560
Kitten,

335
00:18:05,560 --> 00:18:07,360
I brought you walnut milk today.

336
00:18:13,520 --> 00:18:14,840
He loves sweets,

337
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:16,560
loves Qingbuliang.

338
00:18:17,280 --> 00:18:18,280
He loves to laugh.

339
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:20,760
He doesn't like being alone.

340
00:18:21,520 --> 00:18:23,080
What he looks forward to most every day

341
00:18:23,080 --> 00:18:24,810
is being with his good friends.

342
00:18:26,320 --> 00:18:27,280
Xiaochao.

343
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:28,920
Xiaochao.

344
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:31,520
Xiaochao.

345
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:38,040
Xiaochao.

346
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:39,400
Xiaochao.

347
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:41,240
Zhang Chao.

348
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:43,520
Xiaochao.

349
00:18:44,360 --> 00:18:45,560
Xiaochao, Xiaohao.

350
00:18:46,360 --> 00:18:47,640
Xiaochao, come out.

351
00:18:47,840 --> 00:18:49,120
Xiaochao, come out.

352
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:51,000
I'm right here.

353
00:18:52,040 --> 00:18:52,840
Xiaochao.

354
00:18:53,320 --> 00:18:53,980
Zhang Chao.

355
00:18:54,560 --> 00:18:56,280
I've always been here.

356
00:18:56,280 --> 00:18:57,760
Xiaohao.

357
00:19:12,640 --> 00:19:13,960
Zhang Chao.

358
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:15,120
Enough.

359
00:19:20,840 --> 00:19:22,240
What's wrong with you?

360
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:25,800
Sorry,

361
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:27,000
I'm not feeling well.

362
00:19:43,360 --> 00:19:45,440
Hey, no diving here.

363
00:20:19,560 --> 00:20:21,520
Come here.

364
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:22,680
Serves you right.

365
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:31,660
Serves you right. You can't even swim over here.

366
00:20:57,240 --> 00:20:57,960
Hey,

367
00:20:58,080 --> 00:20:58,840
Hey,

368
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:00,440
can you hear me?

369
00:21:02,960 --> 00:21:03,840
Hey,

370
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:05,440
wake up.

371
00:21:05,960 --> 00:21:07,120
We're in trouble.

372
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:08,200
What do we do?

373
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:20,210
You scared me to death. You're finally awake.

374
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:22,800
How are you?

375
00:21:24,440 --> 00:21:25,480
Take it easy.

376
00:21:29,840 --> 00:21:32,100
What were you doing in the water just now?

377
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:35,640
Holding my breath.

378
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:37,600
You shouldn't hold it like that.

379
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:39,600
An average person can only do it for two minutes,

380
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:40,880
and someone professional like me,

381
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:42,080
three to five minutes.

382
00:21:42,080 --> 00:21:44,080
I'm telling you, it's a good thing I have sharp eyes.

383
00:21:44,080 --> 00:21:45,360
Otherwise you would have lost motor control.

384
00:21:45,360 --> 00:21:46,760
A bit later and you would have fainted,

385
00:21:46,760 --> 00:21:47,760
and no one could have saved you.

386
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:48,520
You know?

387
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:51,920
Thank you.

388
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:55,330
I want to calm down for a bit.

389
00:21:59,440 --> 00:22:00,320
Take your time.

390
00:22:00,840 --> 00:22:01,880
Next time,

391
00:22:01,880 --> 00:22:03,200
if you want to practice holding your breath, come to me.

392
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:05,200
I'm a professional, I'll teach you.

393
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:07,300
It's too dangerous to do it like this.

394
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:10,530
I'll let you know in advance next time.

395
00:22:20,760 --> 00:22:21,920
Hello, who is it?

396
00:22:23,720 --> 00:22:24,920
Sir,

397
00:22:24,920 --> 00:22:25,840
hello.

398
00:22:27,080 --> 00:22:28,360
There's a dorm available?

399
00:22:28,360 --> 00:22:30,360
I can do it anytime.

400
00:22:31,360 --> 00:22:32,360
Okay.

401
00:22:32,360 --> 00:22:33,160
Goodbye, sir.

402
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:34,400
Goodbye.

403
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:38,200
Great, I have a dorm now.

404
00:22:42,640 --> 00:22:43,320
Come in.

405
00:22:46,840 --> 00:22:47,600
Xiaobai,

406
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:48,840
you came at the right time.

407
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:50,280
I have many topics here.

408
00:22:50,280 --> 00:22:51,720
See which one you like.

409
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:53,440
I want to resign.

410
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:54,360
What?

411
00:22:55,640 --> 00:22:57,280
If you're unhappy with your work,

412
00:22:57,280 --> 00:22:58,720
you can talk to me.

413
00:22:59,240 --> 00:23:00,520
Don't be impulsive.

414
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:02,560
I'm a bit tired, Team Leader.

415
00:23:03,080 --> 00:23:04,400
And compared to work,

416
00:23:05,240 --> 00:23:07,170
I have more important things to do.

417
00:23:08,440 --> 00:23:09,280
Xiaobai,

418
00:23:09,280 --> 00:23:10,560
think about it again.

419
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:13,200
Think about it again.

420
00:23:39,240 --> 00:23:41,570
Shouldn't you be at the company right now?

421
00:23:43,080 --> 00:23:43,940
What about you?

422
00:23:44,320 --> 00:23:45,440
At this time,

423
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:47,280
shouldn't you be at the TV station?

424
00:23:47,280 --> 00:23:48,280
You already know.

425
00:23:48,560 --> 00:23:49,800
Resigning is a big deal.

426
00:23:49,800 --> 00:23:51,400
Why didn't you tell me first?

427
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:52,600
I'm 22.

428
00:23:52,600 --> 00:23:54,400
I don't need to tell you everything.

429
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:55,330
I didn't mean...

430
00:23:57,320 --> 00:23:58,800
That's not what I meant.

431
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:02,320
Alright.

432
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:04,760
If you're not happy at the TV station,

433
00:24:04,760 --> 00:24:05,560
don't go back.

434
00:24:06,240 --> 00:24:07,480
Come to the Lin Group.

435
00:24:07,480 --> 00:24:08,240
No need.

436
00:24:09,240 --> 00:24:11,240
I've already found what I want to do.

437
00:24:47,960 --> 00:24:50,200
You must be tired from your internship today.

438
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:53,520
Let me give my bestie a heartwarming massage.

439
00:24:53,520 --> 00:24:55,080
Technician No. 13.

440
00:24:55,080 --> 00:24:56,720
Please press harder here.

441
00:24:57,920 --> 00:24:59,400
You little brat, Bai Qiu!

442
00:24:59,800 --> 00:25:00,760
I'm giving you a massage,

443
00:25:00,760 --> 00:25:01,920
and you treat me like a technician!

444
00:25:01,920 --> 00:25:03,520
Why are you so fierce?

445
00:25:05,160 --> 00:25:06,640
Careful with my necklace.

446
00:25:07,160 --> 00:25:08,040
Let me see.

447
00:25:09,280 --> 00:25:10,480
It's so pretty.

448
00:25:12,040 --> 00:25:13,480
Who gave you this necklace?

449
00:25:13,480 --> 00:25:15,160
They have such good taste.

450
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:17,040
Who do you think?

451
00:25:18,720 --> 00:25:20,120
Could it be me?

452
00:25:21,560 --> 00:25:22,440
How is it?

453
00:25:22,440 --> 00:25:23,640
Is the pressure okay?

454
00:25:23,880 --> 00:25:24,440
Yes.

455
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:26,740
Here, press here a few more times.

456
00:25:34,840 --> 00:25:36,160
No peeking.

457
00:25:37,840 --> 00:25:38,640
Okay.

458
00:25:41,440 --> 00:25:42,640
Can I open my eyes now?

459
00:25:43,200 --> 00:25:45,330
Open them when I count down from three.

460
00:25:49,120 --> 00:25:50,840
Happy birthday, Shasha.

461
00:25:52,280 --> 00:25:54,080
What a beautiful cake!

462
00:25:55,120 --> 00:25:56,120
And this.

463
00:25:58,680 --> 00:25:59,680
How do you like it?

464
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:03,000
You really splurged.

465
00:26:03,360 --> 00:26:05,200
This necklace must be very expensive, right?

466
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:06,280
It's nothing.

467
00:26:06,760 --> 00:26:08,120
You deserve the best.

468
00:26:08,480 --> 00:26:09,440
Come here.

469
00:26:09,440 --> 00:26:10,500
Let me put it on you.

470
00:26:15,480 --> 00:26:16,680
When it's your birthday,

471
00:26:16,680 --> 00:26:19,120
I won't be able to afford such an expensive gift.

472
00:26:19,120 --> 00:26:20,280
You don't need to.

473
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:23,280
Meeting you is already the best gift for me.

474
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:27,210
Come, let me take a look.

475
00:26:28,680 --> 00:26:29,840
You're never allowed to take it off.

476
00:26:29,840 --> 00:26:30,680
Okay.

477
00:26:31,080 --> 00:26:32,940
I won't take it off even when I die.

478
00:26:34,600 --> 00:26:36,360
Don't say such unlucky things.

479
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:41,240
I'm back!

480
00:26:42,760 --> 00:26:43,840
Shasha,

481
00:26:43,840 --> 00:26:45,880
look what I brought for you.

482
00:26:55,080 --> 00:26:55,760
Hello?

483
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:57,960
Who is this?

484
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:01,000
Are you a family member of the deceased?

485
00:27:01,760 --> 00:27:02,840
W-What?

486
00:27:04,120 --> 00:27:06,400
The owner of this phone was just in a car accident,

487
00:27:06,400 --> 00:27:08,000
and has been confirmed dead.

488
00:27:28,320 --> 00:27:29,120
Hello?

489
00:27:29,800 --> 00:27:31,360
910 Changyang Road.

490
00:27:31,920 --> 00:27:32,560
Okay.

491
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:33,690
I'll be right there.

492
00:27:36,360 --> 00:27:37,420
Something came up.

493
00:27:37,680 --> 00:27:40,140
Can you take a cab back to school by yourself?

494
00:27:42,560 --> 00:27:43,620
I'm talking to you.

495
00:27:44,440 --> 00:27:44,920
Okay.

496
00:27:47,600 --> 00:27:48,840
Just drop me off here.

497
00:27:50,240 --> 00:27:50,960
Pull over.

498
00:27:59,480 --> 00:28:01,010
Let me know when you arrive.

499
00:28:08,240 --> 00:28:08,920
Brother.

500
00:28:08,920 --> 00:28:11,120
I met a girl at the coffee shop recently.

501
00:28:11,160 --> 00:28:12,220
She's very pretty.

502
00:28:12,640 --> 00:28:13,720
I was thinking

503
00:28:14,080 --> 00:28:15,880
whether I should introduce you two.

504
00:28:15,880 --> 00:28:17,040
I don't have time.

505
00:28:17,360 --> 00:28:19,360
I'm extremely busy with the company.

506
00:28:19,360 --> 00:28:20,640
Just take a look.

507
00:28:20,640 --> 00:28:21,840
She's really pretty.

508
00:28:23,520 --> 00:28:24,320
Very pretty.

509
00:28:27,440 --> 00:28:28,440
What do you think?

510
00:28:34,800 --> 00:28:36,120
Not as pretty as you.

511
00:28:38,640 --> 00:28:40,080
If you're going to find someone for me,

512
00:28:40,080 --> 00:28:42,680
you should find someone better than yourself.

513
00:28:43,120 --> 00:28:44,120
Go to sleep early.

514
00:28:44,240 --> 00:28:45,570
Good night. Good night.

515
00:28:55,400 --> 00:28:56,480
What?

516
00:28:57,320 --> 00:28:59,600
You want to see my dad's dashcam?

517
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:03,320
I want to know

518
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:05,800
if my brother is dating someone.

519
00:29:08,840 --> 00:29:09,840
Well...

520
00:29:11,280 --> 00:29:12,160
Don't worry.

521
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:13,890
I'm not trying to break them up.

522
00:29:15,800 --> 00:29:17,040
The truth is,

523
00:29:18,600 --> 00:29:21,060
my parents passed away when I was very young.

524
00:29:21,760 --> 00:29:23,360
My brother is my only family.

525
00:29:24,040 --> 00:29:25,700
He has sacrificed a lot for me.

526
00:29:26,120 --> 00:29:27,440
I really hope

527
00:29:27,760 --> 00:29:29,360
he can find someone he likes.

528
00:29:31,040 --> 00:29:32,680
The other day in the car,

529
00:29:32,680 --> 00:29:34,480
I saw some women's stuff.

530
00:29:35,840 --> 00:29:36,400
So...

531
00:29:36,400 --> 00:29:37,240
I get it.

532
00:29:38,640 --> 00:29:40,200
You want to know

533
00:29:40,200 --> 00:29:42,800
what kind of relationship your brother has with this girl.

534
00:29:42,800 --> 00:29:43,640
Yes.

535
00:29:44,560 --> 00:29:45,600
Can you help me?

536
00:29:45,600 --> 00:29:46,330
Don't worry.

537
00:29:46,720 --> 00:29:47,680
Leave it to me.

538
00:29:47,680 --> 00:29:49,210
I'll figure something out.

539
00:29:51,320 --> 00:29:52,240
Great.

540
00:29:52,240 --> 00:29:52,920
Thank you.

541
00:29:58,960 --> 00:29:59,760
Weihao!

542
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:02,600
Li Weihao.

543
00:30:04,080 --> 00:30:05,210
Sorry to bother you.

544
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:07,320
I just wanted to ask

545
00:30:07,560 --> 00:30:10,160
how the thing I asked you for last time is going.

546
00:30:10,680 --> 00:30:12,120
The dashcam.

547
00:30:12,120 --> 00:30:12,880
I checked it.

548
00:30:13,560 --> 00:30:14,760
They were just regular clients.

549
00:30:14,760 --> 00:30:15,760
Nothing special.

550
00:30:17,640 --> 00:30:20,170
Then can you give me the footage from that day?

551
00:30:20,800 --> 00:30:21,680
Well...

552
00:30:24,080 --> 00:30:25,640
I... I... I'll try my best.

553
00:30:26,840 --> 00:30:29,040
Yeah, there's really nothing special.

554
00:30:33,280 --> 00:30:34,120
By the way,

555
00:30:34,120 --> 00:30:36,280
did you get the stuff

556
00:30:36,280 --> 00:30:37,480
I asked for last time?

557
00:30:40,280 --> 00:30:42,280
I might need some more time for this.

558
00:30:45,880 --> 00:30:47,840
Does Li Weihao know something?

559
00:30:48,720 --> 00:30:51,120
These things are too much of a coincidence.

560
00:30:51,480 --> 00:30:53,080
The cause of Shasha's death,

561
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:54,520
I must find out.

562
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:13,680
What are you doing?

563
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:14,740
Are you moving out?

564
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:18,280
I rented a place off-campus.

565
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:21,060
I won't be living here for a while.

566
00:31:22,200 --> 00:31:23,440
Did you ask me?

567
00:31:23,440 --> 00:31:25,100
Did I agree to let you move out?

568
00:31:26,560 --> 00:31:28,360
Brother, can you stop bossing me around all the time?

569
00:31:28,360 --> 00:31:29,880
I'm not a kid anymore.

570
00:31:31,720 --> 00:31:33,200
What else do you want to do?

571
00:31:33,200 --> 00:31:36,730
Are we going to live together like this for the rest of our lives?

572
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:50,040
Miss, let me do it.

573
00:31:50,040 --> 00:31:52,080
Thank you, Uncle Li.

574
00:31:52,080 --> 00:31:52,840
Come.

575
00:32:08,600 --> 00:32:09,480
Here.

576
00:32:43,240 --> 00:32:44,240
Did you two fight?

577
00:32:48,240 --> 00:32:49,600
Cherish it well.

578
00:32:50,520 --> 00:32:51,850
Life is unpredictable.

579
00:32:52,880 --> 00:32:54,200
I wish I could talk to

580
00:32:54,200 --> 00:32:55,680
Weihao right now,

581
00:32:56,640 --> 00:32:58,320
even if it's an argument.

582
00:33:01,200 --> 00:33:02,040
Uncle Li.

583
00:33:02,600 --> 00:33:03,800
After what happened,

584
00:33:05,040 --> 00:33:07,370
you should rest at home for a few more days.

585
00:33:09,760 --> 00:33:11,120
Being at home

586
00:33:11,120 --> 00:33:12,520
only makes me overthink.

587
00:33:13,080 --> 00:33:14,410
Coming out to see people

588
00:33:14,480 --> 00:33:15,880
makes me feel better.

589
00:33:24,520 --> 00:33:25,320
Uncle Li,

590
00:33:26,040 --> 00:33:28,040
could you help me buy a cup of coffee?

591
00:33:28,640 --> 00:33:29,360
Okay.

592
00:33:41,640 --> 00:33:42,640
This is too much.

593
00:33:42,640 --> 00:33:43,880
It's fine, Uncle Li.

594
00:33:43,880 --> 00:33:45,280
Buy one for yourself too.

595
00:33:45,560 --> 00:33:46,480
Thank you.

596
00:34:05,200 --> 00:34:06,160
It was deleted.

597
00:34:12,840 --> 00:34:14,170
Coconut milk with rice,

598
00:34:14,280 --> 00:34:15,520
your favorite when you were a kid.

599
00:34:15,520 --> 00:34:16,719
I just made it for you.

600
00:34:18,840 --> 00:34:20,440
Take it away. I'm not eating.

601
00:34:26,560 --> 00:34:27,239
Chao.

602
00:34:29,480 --> 00:34:32,520
I feel like you're different from when you were little.

603
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:33,239
You've changed.
